This paper deals with designing and analyzing algorithms for regularized loss minimization problems, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of sampling-based algorithms and coreset construction, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of these algorithms in computational models for large data, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or systems and control (cs.SI).
